
[1]aggravation

   AGGRAVA'TION, n.

   1. The act of making worse, used of evils, natural or moral; the act of
   increasing severity or hainousness; addition to that which is evil or
   improper; as, an aggravation of pain or grief.

   2. Exaggerated representation, or heightened description of any thing
   wrong, improper, or unnatural; as, an aggravation of features in a
   caricature.
